SUMMARY:Davis Forest School Spring Programs Registration Open
DESCRIPTION:Registration is open for Davis Forest School Spring 2026 programs! This spring we are offering our: \n– After School Program in Davis\, Orangevale/Folsom and Sacramento. This program is characterized by a thoughtful blend of child-led exploration with elements of naturalist studies\, nature connection routines\, earth skills\, and imaginative play. We have programs available for 5 – 12 year olds\, with different age groupings to choose from and staggered drop-off/pick-up times. Most kids come once a week\, but you are welcome to register for as many sessions as you like. \n– Parent/Child Program in Davis\, Sacramento\, Folsom\, Lincoln/Rocklin\, and West Roseville. This program features nurturing and community-building facilitated weekly sessions for families with babies and young children. The program is geared at ages 0-6\, but all ages are welcome. \n– Homeschool Days Program in Davis\, Folsom Lake\, Sacramento\, and Lincoln/Rocklin. Like our after-school programs\, Homeschool Days is characterized by a thoughtful blend of child-led exploration with elements of naturalist studies\, nature connection routines\, earth skills\, and imaginative play. Our Lincoln location offers a class for 5 – 12 year olds and our other locations are geared for 7 – 12 year olds\, with younger children being considered on a case-by-case basis. Most kids come once a week\, but you are welcome to register for as many sessions as you like. \nPlease visit our website for more details and to register.
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/davis-forest-school-spring-programs-registration-open/
LOCATION:CA
CATEGORIES:Bring the Kids,Community,Outside
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Muddyfeet-scaled.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Forest School":MAILTO:programs@davisforestschool.org
END:VEVENT
