SUMMARY:Free\, public forum with author Javier Zamora
DESCRIPTION:UC Davis and the city of Davis are hosting a free\, public forum with author Javier Zamora to bring people together to discuss belonging in Davis public education systems and communities. Memoirist\, poet\, and speaker Javier Zamora believes that immigrants must keep ownership of their own stories. In his award-winning memoir\, Solito\, he explores his harrowing journey to the United States as an unaccompanied 9-year-old that gives a unique and unforgettable glimpse into the realities of child migration.
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/free-public-forum-with-author-javier-zamora/
LOCATION:Davis Veterans Memorial Theatre\, 203 E. 14th Street\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
CATEGORIES:Books & Talks
ORGANIZER;CN="UC Davis and the City of Davis":MAILTO:foacommunications@ucdavis.edu
END:VEVENT
